On Saturday, March 19, 2005, at 08:07AM, Meg and Leigh <alshouse(-at-)speakeasy.net> wrote:

>Hi,
>Well I have a problem with my passenger side tail light. The running light and
>side marker light are out but when you put on the breaks the break light
>works. I checked and cleaned all the bulbs and cleaned the ground connection
>to the tail light housing. No go anyone have this problem before and can help?
>It used to be intermittent and I thought it was that a bulb was loose which
>worked once but now that didn't work must have been luck or something. My bus
>is a 1977 FI Westy.

I had this problem on the 72 bus. In addition we would have brake lights or backup lights but not both. I removed both housings and the side marker housing, cleaned all the connectors and recrimped the sidemarker wiring and now everything works.

